entries.femaleVariant: V! Got somethin' for you.
Of course, can't let the crowd down.
Right. Can't let that full house down.
Honestly, got no idea who these people are.
Just strays. Kerry didn't want word to get around.
Better worry about whoever's standin' in for Henry.
Better worry about whoever's standin' in for Denny.
I'd worry more about Denny's replacement.
I'd worry more about Henry's replacement.
Ready to thrash?
Dunno if this is a good idea.
I dunno, maybe this isn't such a good idea.
Now you mention it?
Have fun.
Let's motor.
And that's when the groupie started cryin'.
Her friend's like, "Come on, bagged him, didn't ya? What's wrong?"
You have a good time?
Have a good time?
Hell yeah! Kerry even said I'ma see some eddies!
What's your plan now?
So what's the plan now?
Get wiped. Kerry's tab. Heheheh.
No, no, I hit it too hard.
It was fine, great.
You were great.
You were great.
Ooh, first time I've ever heard that after a gig.
Thanks.
Axe went outta tune after "Chippin' In."
No worries. Can't hear the bass anyway.
I mean... Shit, never heard anything like it.
And you're not likely to again.
Well? I do all right?
Well? I do all right?
Mhm. Too damn well.
Got me wonderin' where Kerry's been hidin' you all this time.
Yeah, well we'll see about that.
Ya think the media caught wind of this?
I know him, seen him play.
And? He any good?
Kerry got Drausin from Cutthroat to join us.
He's... fine. Just... fine. You're the mystery dish, here.
Pill time. Just be discreet.
And if I start puking blood again?
Don't go making a scene. This is Kerry's big night.
It's getting worse. Maybe this gig isn't worth it?
Fine. Go out and play. I'll just sit back, tend to my bleedin' ears.
OK, fine. You got me.
How're ya feelin'? Ready for the show?
Hey, V.
Uh, and you are...?
How're you feelin' ahead of the show?
entries.maleVariant: How ya feelin' ahead of the show?

entries.femaleVariant: You and Denny – what happened?
Wanna tell me what happened with Henry?
How 'bout you tell me what happened with Henry.
Weird. Like I'm about to pretend to be… myself.
I got a feeling Nancy doesn't think I can keep up with 'em.
entries.maleVariant: Got a feeling Nancy doesn't think I can keep up with 'em.

entries.femaleVariant: Well, she's right.
Plus, Johnny's out.
Never thought I'd say I miss the bastard, but I damn well do.
Ancient history. Kept falling into all sorts of crap, then I'd have to dig him out.
Got tired of getting your hands dirty all the time?
entries.maleVariant: You got tired of getting your hands dirty all the time?

entries.femaleVariant: All wrong. Managed to get him a gig with a decent band.
Henry quit usin', got his shit together, things were goin' great. So he booted me out of his life.
Then what happened?
Stopped needing you.
What happened next?
Stopped needing you.
For a little. Made it a month partying with his new pals.
Then they tossed 'im out 'cause he started acting up again.
You get off on this sort of drama? He ditched me, partied with his new pals for a month.
Ran into him on the street, total mess. Gonk even fainted for effect, a tug at my heartstrings.
What'd you do?
Left him right there. And made damn sure he couldn't find me again.
V. We met at Denny's?
Oh, right. Shit was fucked up, wasn't it?
See you're in great shape today.
You look to be in great shape today.
Yeah, yep. Kerry took care of me.
Didn't he just get you outta detox?
Uh-huh. But I'm done with all that stuff anyways.
Kerry's got waaaay better goods. Pure as gold.
What happened with Denny? Meanin' before you filled her pool with concrete.
I hit bottom, she left me.
Almost flatlined right there in the street, and she just stepped around me like so much trash.
What happened to you then?
Actually, heard Denny took care of you a lot.
What happened to you then?
Now, I heard Denny looked after you, lots.
Dunno, I was on some bad shit, collapsed.
They brought me back, but Denny was gone.
Yeah. Musta finally got bored. Just picked the worst possible time.
Her friends wouldn't talk to me. Like I'd disappeared or died.
There you are.
This is Drausin, from Cutthroat.
Think my shakes're the same or worse.
Hey. Big fan, huge fan. You too? Got all their albums, I mean, I never dreamed I'd…
[Start concert] All right. Let's go.
All right. Let's do this.
Crowd got you stressed? Or is it me?
Fuck you.
And missed you, too.
Fuck. This is fucked up.
What is?
Wanna do an encore gig?
Losers always say they were just there to have a good time.
Wanna do it again?
Actually, uh... got pretty nervous for this thing.
Felt like I had something to prove – to myself, to you and whoever the fuck.
But all I did was have a good time. That's it.
Losers always say that – just did it to have a good time.
Huh? No. That was enough.
Still think you're better'n me?
Damn right I do. But maybe this'll help.
V, how you feelin'?
Can't believe that asshole Kerry just up and left you like this.
Ya wanna hear a new…? Johnny?
He's gone, isn't he?
Take care, V. I'll be in touch.
In that case... here, take it. As a souvenir.
You sure?
Won't play without you. Just wouldn't be the same.
See what you're doin' here. But I still plan on playin'.
[Take] Oh, you shouldn't have.
How was the concert?
You shouldn't have, really.
How was the gig?
The very gun I tried to shoot Johnny with – when he broke into my house.
Hella preem. Heheh, Samurai's found its new groove.
Damn shame I had to miss it.
Eh, can still come to my show.
Cool. Feel like I fell asleep and woke up fifty years later.
Back to work, then.
Looked like Kerry was in a big hurry.
Hope you're done makin' last requests.
Guess he had somewhere to be, badly.
Hope that's it for last requests. Not sure I can handle any more.
Probably writing a new song as we speak.
Isn't that what you wanted? To make him feel better?
It is. And I'm starting to regret you agreed to this concert thing.
Better, but not that good.
"Johnny, don't ever leave me again! I can't live without you"?
A little of that could go a long way.
Huh, here I thought I'd hear "Thank you, V." Said it was important to you, this thing with Kerry.
It was. But not more important than you.
Kerry's got his life back. Whereas we should be worryin' about how to get yours back.
Dunno if you know, but once upon a time this was Silverhand's.
Where's Kerry?
Told me you play really well.
Better be true, 'cause there won't be a dress rehearsal.
Where's Kerry?
Should be here any minute.
Thanks for putting the gig together.
entries.maleVariant: Hey, thanks for putting the gig together.

entries.femaleVariant: Fuck. Nancy just gets shit done.
Thanks for putting all this together.
Where'd you find it? It's, like, fresh off the shelf.
Should just whisper "Mikoshi" in her ear, we'll be all set.
Bought it, private collection. Always like to have everything down to the last detail.
Gets too obsessed at times, but gotta respect her hustle.
Please. Kerry couldn't twiddle his own asshole without my help.
Silverhand was prolly the same.
Heh, worse. At least Kerry did what I told him to do, kept outta my hair.
DeLuze Orphean. Where'd you find it?
DeLuze Orphean. 'Member that Samurai graffiti in Heywood  where the bakery used to be?
Uh-huh. Got painted over a while ago. But yeah, Johnny was holding the Orphean there. Nice one.
And the groupie's like, "He said he was with the band! But he plays bass!" Hahaha.
Chill, choom. She's in the same boat as you.
entries.maleVariant: Chill, choom. He's in the same boat as you.

entries.femaleVariant: Wanna talk to a star, talk to me. And get that shakin' under control.
Maybe you should hang onto this, actually.
Yeah. Yeah, but he can still hear you.
Thanks, but not in the mood for hovering tables and voices from beyond the grave right now.
Meanin' you tried to shoot me.
Yeah, and earlier... Eh, never mind.
Well? Wasn't so bad, was it?
Too bad Ker's gone off.
Hope that's it for last requests.
Maybe. Now you get a chance to do what you will.
Gotta go talk to Hanako. Fast.
OK. Your choice.
For sure. Hyenas.
Let's go.

[Take pills] Have fun.
